<br>
This doesn't mean your totally sunk, however! Since there are some hosts that are still good for file linking, and other hosts that put reasonable amounts of advertising on your website, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  it is a good idea to use a separate provider for image linking and web pages.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE CENTER START--><center>  Where should I host my images?</center><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I could answer this question here, but ezBoard's staff constantly are updating the following list of sites and what they can do for your images. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://beta.ezboard.com/fezboardfrm36.showMessage?topicID=28.topic">Click here for the list!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Alternatively, and a lot of people are going in this direction, you can trick most any server into letting you outside link your images. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Be warned, however, this is often against a host's TOS (terms of service), and if they find your site doing it, they may cancel your services and delete your account.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> If this does not discourage you, the procedure is as follows:<br>
<br>
1) Save your image in a format that is proper for web use (JPG or GIF compression).<br>
2) Upload the file to your web space provider.<br>
3) Re-name the file and change the extension to .txt<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Example: You upload mypic.jpg to your Geocities site. You rename it mypic.txt</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
4) Whenever you want people to see your image on this board, just link it like it's an image.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Example: &lt;IMAGE&gt;www.geocities.com/myaccount/mypic.txt&lt;/IMAGE&gt; (but replace the carrots &lt;&gt; with brackets [] )</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Example 2: Rename the file to mypic.htm, and follow the same procedure. Naming them to html files </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->may<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  make it more difficult for them to catch your site doing this.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE CENTER START--><center>  Where should I host my website for FREE?</center><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
If you ARE NOT willing to pay any money for your web site, you should read <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://100best-free-web-space.com/Top10_get_real.htm">this information</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. The economics of today's web make it impossible for companies to provide free web space with no ads. Once you know what you can expect, just browse through their <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://100best-free-web-space.com/">arcives and site ratings</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. Note that not <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  every</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> site they list is free, so you might have to go down the list a little.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE CENTER START--><center>  What hosts provide low-cost hosting, but allow for both outside linking and advertisement-free websites?</center><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
If you ARE willing and able to pay for a web host, there are plenty of good providers who will host you a registered domain for free with no advertisements. This means you get www.yoursite.com, can outside link images, and can build a web site without advertisements. The actual hosting of the site is free, but you have to pay the DNS, which keeps track of domain information and directs traffic across the web, somewhere between $10 and $30 per year, depending where you get it. Don't ask me where to get it cheapest, I don't know. Most such sites, for example <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.doteasy.com"> DotEasy</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> allow you to register your domain <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  though them</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and often this means you get it a little cheaper.<br>
<br>
There are some small catches to the free domain providers, and you can find out the details on their sites. A lot of the best such providers are listed at the top of the following site:<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://100best-free-web-space.com/">100best-free-web-space.com/</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Where do I host my images/site? If you do have a little extra money to spend, you might want to sign up for a cheap domain host that has a monthly hosting fee. You get many more features, like CGI, PHP, and a bunch of other things I don't understand, but you also get <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  more space and more data transfer allowed.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I used to host with DotEasy.com, which is still a good, free domain provider with a yearly DNS fee, but they now will allow you only 1 GB of transfer per month, after which they cut off your services. That's enough for smaller sites, but as mine grows, I felt it better to go to a site that allows 6 Gb of transfer per month. I host with http://www.your-site.com/ and they've been pretty good. Might want to shop around, though, there is probably better out there if you've got the money. Just... don't go and spend $30+ a month for the king size hosting package if you don't even know what you want to put on your site. It's really not a good investment.<br>
<br>
Sorry this is so long, there is just a lot of things that must be considered, and some different options I hope you will take advantage of. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
